                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/4391: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-02T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 2, 1929—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>46. Referring to telegram No. 30, April 1, 9 p.m. from Legation at Tegucigalpa.
                    The Department is replying as follows:</p>
                <p>[Here follows substance of telegram No. 26, April 2, 1 p.m., to the Minister in
                    Honduras printed <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>]</p>
                <p>Please inform the Department at once whether there has been any friction along
                    the frontier which would afford a basis for the statements of the Honduran
                    Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
